<id>http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=1125&amp;p=9706#p9706</id>
<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=1125&amp;p=9706#p9706"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[NSF2MIDI]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=1125&amp;p=9706#p9706"><![CDATA[
It's been tried before. Turns out it's hard in the general case to recognize what constitutes a "note" based on just the writes to the PSG registers. Go download (say) the Silver Surfer NSF, listen to each channel in Festalon or another NSF player plug-in, and tell me how you'd pick out individual notes.<br /><br />The most plausible way to enhance NES music using MIDI would be to make a mapper with a 16550 UART or other serial port controller and then ROM-hack your games to write a MIDI bitstream to the serial port.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Fri Feb 17, 2006 7:39 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
